The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Close shave for Madhab 

A STAFF REPORTER 

Calcutta: Mohammedan Sporting defender Madhab Das had a close shave in the NFL match against Sporting Clube de Goa on Saturday. Midway through the second half, Madhab fell to the ground after trying to chest a powerful shot and lost consciousness. 

His heart stopped beating He regained consciousness only after receiving emergency assistance on field, club secretary Sultan Ahmed said. He did, however, continue playing. 

Ahmed said that Madhab was fine. 

A chest X-ray was done and the report didnt reveal anything serious. I talked to the coach (Biswajit Bhattacharya) and he said Madhab may play the Churchill match (on Thursday), Ahmed said. 




